f2026584-253a-4514-bb20-519ab8096937.33551d0c-953e-441a-90c8-b02e3f4b1889.description=
This operation starts the OSBuildPlan on the given unprovisioned server in the SA.
This Operation is supported for SA 9.0 or later.



Inputs\:
coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service.
corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443'
coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS'
coreUsername - Username of the SA.
corePassword - Password of SA user.
coreVersion - [Optional] SA version. By default, it is the SA version being used.
osbpPath - Complete path of the OS Build Plan.
osbpID - The ID of the OS Build Plan. If provided, the 'osbpPath' is ignored.
unprovisionedServer - Names of SA unprovisioned servers(separated by 'separator').
unprovisionedServerID - [Optional] The IDs of SA unprovisioned servers(separated by 'separator'). If this input is provided, then 'unprovisionedServer' is ignored.
timeout - [Optional] Operation timeout in milliseconds. If it is zero (0), the operation will return immediately. By default it is '300000'.
jobTimeout - [Optional] SA job timeout in milliseconds. If it is zero (0), the default timeout value from SA will be used.
osbpApxParam - [Optional] Extra arguments to the Program APX command used to execute the OSBuildPlan.
separator - The separator used for separating the inputs that support list values. The default value for the separator is a comma (,).
ticketID - The ticket ID for this job. If not specified it will be set to the default value\: 'Starting OSBP by SA user .
notificationFailureOwner - The email address of the owner of the job when the job failed.
notificationSuccessOwner - The email address of the owner of the job when the job succeeded.
notificationCancelOwner - The email address of the owner of the job when the job was canceled.
notificationFailureRecipients - The email addresses to notify when the job failed.
notificationSuccessRecipients - The email addresses to notify when the job succeeded.
notificationCancelRecipients - The email addresses to notify when the job was canceled.
scheduleDateYear - The year to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. This input must be provided for setting a job schedule.
scheduleDateMonth - The month to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 1 and 12. This input must be provided for setting a job schedule.
scheduleDateDayOfMonth - The day to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 1 and 31. This input must be provided for setting a job schedule.
scheduleDateHour - The hour to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 0 and 23. If not set, it will have the default value 0.
scheduleDateMinute - The minute to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 0 and 59. If not set, it will have the default value 0.
scheduleDateSecond - The second to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 0 and 59. If not set, it will have the default value 0.
scheduleDateTimezone - The time zone used to express the job schedule date. If not set, it will have the default value GMT.

Outputs\:
status - Operation completion Status.
idSaJob - The id of the SA job that was created.


Responses\:
success - Operation passed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status'
failure - Operation failed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status' and 'exception'
f2026584-253a-4514-bb20-519ab8096937.684800ef-edc7-43f4-a3a1-ac376bf2b603.prompt=Password of SA user. f2026584-253a-4514-bb20-519ab8096937.9d8d65ed-d770-4db9-841a-e9a7a8e0921d.description=Waits for the job to reach a specific state. If no state is specified, then this will wait for the job to reach an end state. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. jobID - The id of the job. status - The status to wait for the job to reach. If none is specified this will wait until the job is no longer running. timeout - The maximum number of milliseconds to wait for the job. If not specified, 1 hour is used. frequency - The frequency, in milliseconds, with which the operation will check if the job has reached the specified state (or an end state). The default value is 5000 ms. Responses\: failure - Something went wrong. success - The operation completed successfully. f2026584-253a-4514-bb20-519ab8096937.aad601b8-54b1-4650-978e-722cf1486b65.prompt=Username of the SA. f2026584-253a-4514-bb20-519ab8096937.aec9eeed-a621-44a2-8d68-3ba0988305cb.description=
Switches the host power on or off, using the Proliant iLO processor. 

Inputs\:
    host - The target Proliant iLO processor.
    username - The iLO user name.
    password - The iLO password associated with the  input value.
    port - The SSL port.
Default value\: 443
    hostPower - The host's desired power state. 
Valid values\: Yes, No, On, Off
    force - Forces the power state change, using the virtual power press and hold method. 
Valid values\: Yes, No
Default value\: No

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. An empty string, if the operation completed successfully. Otherwise, it contains a message indicating failure reason.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.  See  for details.
